HEADWORD: Tubicorn
<hw>Tu"bi*corn</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tubus</ets> tube + <ets>cornu</ets> horn: cf. F.
<ets>tubicorne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any ruminant having
horns composed of a bony axis covered with a horny sheath; a
hollow-horned ruminant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tubicornous</ent>⟦br⟧
